            <div class="alert-box">
                <strong style="color: #991b1b;">Campaign Optimization Required:</strong>
                <div class="two-column" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                    <div>
                        <h4 style="color: #991b1b; margin-bottom: 10px;">BFCM 2025 (2.71x ROAS)</h4>
                        <ul style="font-size: 13px;">
                            <li><strong>Root cause:</strong> Over-reliance on discount messaging diluted brand value; broad cold audiences drove up CPP</li>
                            <li><strong>2026 fix:</strong> Lead with product/styling creative, discount as secondary hook</li>
                            <li><strong>Audience shift:</strong> 80% warm (purchasers, engagers, email) vs 20% cold prospecting</li>
                            <li><strong>Budget increase:</strong> $30K dedicated (6x the $4.7K spent in 2025)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <h4 style="color: #991b1b; margin-bottom: 10px;">Clearance Campaigns (1.64x ROAS)</h4>
                        <ul style="font-size: 13px;">
                            <li><strong>Root cause:</strong> Low-demand products with weak creative; retargeting pools too small</li>
                            <li><strong>2026 fix:</strong> Bundle slow movers with bestsellers ("Complete the Look")</li>
                            <li><strong>Creative approach:</strong> Style clearance items as hero pieces, not "sale" items</li>
                            <li><strong>Budget cap:</strong> Max $500/week on clearance; pause if below 2.5x after 7 days</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="insight-box">
                <strong>Key Insight:</strong> Weekly Arrivals campaigns generate 52% of spend but deliver 52% of purchases at 4.07x ROAS â€” the most efficient high-volume campaign. This aligns perfectly with Teddy & Rose's weekly launch cadence and should be the primary scaling vehicle in 2026.
            </div>

            <h3>Trend Analysis: 90-Day â†’ 30-Day â†’ 14-Day</h3>
