                <strong style="color: #991b1b;">Trend Alert:</strong> Recent 14-day performance shows efficiency decline (3.52x vs 3.91x 90-day average). This is partially seasonal (post-BFCM normalization) but warrants Q1 2026 creative refresh and audience optimization to reverse the trend. Conservative budget approach allows focus on efficiency recovery before scaling.
            </div>

            <div class="strategy-box">
                <strong>Efficiency Recovery Action Plan (Q1 Priority):</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Week 1-2:</strong> Audit all active ad sets â€” pause any with ROAS below 2.5x and spend over $200</li>
                    <li><strong>Week 2-3:</strong> Consolidate budget into top 5 performing ad sets per campaign (reduce fragmentation)</li>
                    <li><strong>Week 3-4:</strong> Launch 3 new creative variations per campaign using proven product categories (sweaters, plaid, outerwear)</li>
                    <li><strong>Ongoing:</strong> Implement weekly ROAS floor check â€” any ad set below 3x for 7 consecutive days gets paused or budget reduced by 50%</li>
                    <li><strong>Target:</strong> Return to 3.8x+ blended ROAS by end of February before any scaling initiatives</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

