            <div class="action-item priority-high">
                <div class="action-title">2. Scale Weekly Arrivals to 55% of Budget</div>
                <div class="action-desc">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Increase Weekly Arrivals daily budget by 15% monthly</li>
                        <li>Implement winner duplication strategy (scale best performers to $400/day)</li>
                        <li>Test 2-week extended run on top ROAS ad sets</li>
                        <li>Develop "Best Sellers" evergreen extension for proven products</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="strategy-box">
                <strong>Weekly Arrivals Scaling Protocol:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Budget Increase Schedule:</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 5px;">
                            <li>April: $1,300/day â†’ May: $1,500/day â†’ June: $1,700/day</li>
                            <li>Rule: Only increase if prior month achieved 3.8x+ ROAS</li>
                            <li>If ROAS drops below 3.5x, pause scaling and return to prior budget</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Winner Duplication Strategy:</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 5px;">
                            <li>Any ad set achieving 5x+ ROAS after $500 spend = "Winner"</li>
                            <li>Duplicate winner ad set and increase budget to $400/day</li>
                            <li>Keep original ad set running at original budget (don't consolidate)</li>
                            <li>Maximum 3 scaled winners running simultaneously</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Extended Run Test:</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 5px;">
                            <li>Select top 2 ROAS ad sets from April Weekly Arrivals</li>
                            <li>Instead of pausing after 1 week, let run for 2 full weeks</li>
                            <li>Track: Does ROAS decline after week 1? At what spend level?</li>
                            <li>Learning: Establish optimal "run length" before creative fatigue</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>"Best Sellers" Evergreen Extension:</strong>
                        <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-top: 5px;">
                            <li>Any product with 10+ purchases and 5x+ ROAS from Weekly Arrivals = Best Seller</li>
                            <li>Move Best Seller creative to Evergreen campaign for continued running</li>
                            <li>This captures long-tail value from winners after Weekly Arrivals cycle ends</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="action-item priority-medium">
                <div class="action-title">3. Retention Campaign Launch</div>
                <div class="action-desc">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Implement 30-day post-purchase retargeting sequence</li>
                        <li>Create "Complete Your Wardrobe" cross-sell campaigns</li>
                        <li>Test VIP/loyalty messaging for repeat customers</li>
                        <li>Target Month 1 retention window (9.1% return rate)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="strategy-box">
                <strong>Retention Campaign Setup Guide:</strong>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Audience 1 - Recent Buyers (7-30 days):</strong> Create custom audience of purchasers excluding last 7 days â†’ show "Complete Your Look" carousel with complementary products to their purchase</li>
                    <li><strong>Audience 2 - Lapsed Buyers (60-90 days):</strong> Create custom audience of purchasers 60-90 days ago â†’ show "We Miss You" creative with new arrivals since their last purchase</li>
                    <li><strong>Audience 3 - VIP Repeat (2+ orders):</strong> Create custom audience of 2+ purchasers â†’ show "Exclusive Early Access" to weekly arrivals 24hrs before public</li>
                    <li><strong>Budget allocation:</strong> $150/day split across 3 audiences ($50 each)</li>
                    <li><strong>Exclusions:</strong> Exclude purchasers from last 7 days from all retention campaigns to avoid over-messaging</li>
                    <li><strong>Expected ROAS:</strong> Retention campaigns should achieve 5-7x ROAS given warm audience â€” if below 4x after 14 days, review creative</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

